com.tencent.map.plugin

类 PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tencent.map.plugin.PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder
  • 封闭类:
    PluginContentProviderOperation

    public static class PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder
extends Object
    Used to add parameters to a ContentProviderOperation. The PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder is first created by calling ContentProviderOperation#newInsert(android.net.Uri), ContentProviderOperation#newUpdate(android.net.Uri), ContentProviderOperation#newDelete(android.net.Uri) or ContentProviderOperation#newAssertQuery(Uri). The withXXX methods can then be used to add parameters to the builder. See the specific methods to find for which PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder type each is allowed. Call build() to create the ContentProviderOperation once all the parameters have been supplied.

    • 方法详细资料

      • build

        public PluginContentProviderOperation build()
        Create a ContentProviderOperation from this PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder.

      • withValueBackReferences

        public PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder withValueBackReferences(ContentValues backReferences)
        Add a ContentValues of back references. The key is the name of the column and the value is an integer that is the index of the previous result whose value should be used for the column. The value is added as a String. A column value from the back references takes precedence over a value specified in withValues(ContentValues). This can only be used with builders of type insert, update, or assert.
        返回:
        this builder, to allow for chaining.

      • withValueBackReference

        public PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder withValueBackReference(String key,
                                                            int previousResult)
        Add a ContentValues back reference. A column value from the back references takes precedence over a value specified in withValues(ContentValues). This can only be used with builders of type insert, update, or assert.
        返回:
        this builder, to allow for chaining.

      • withSelectionBackReference

        public PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder withSelectionBackReference(int selectionArgIndex,
                                                                int previousResult)
        Add a back references as a selection arg. Any value at that index of the selection arg that was specified by withSelection(java.lang.String, java.lang.String[]) will be overwritten. This can only be used with builders of type update, delete, or assert.
        返回:
        this builder, to allow for chaining.

      • withValues

        public PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder withValues(ContentValues values)
        The ContentValues to use. This may be null. These values may be overwritten by the corresponding value specified by withValueBackReference(java.lang.String, int) or by future calls to withValues(ContentValues) or withValue(java.lang.String, java.lang.Object). This can only be used with builders of type insert, update, or assert.
        返回:
        this builder, to allow for chaining.

      • withValue

        public PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder withValue(String key,
                                               Object value)
        A value to insert or update. This value may be overwritten by the corresponding value specified by withValueBackReference(java.lang.String, int). This can only be used with builders of type insert, update, or assert.
        参数:
        key - the name of this value
        value - the value itself. the type must be acceptable for insertion by ContentValues#put
        返回:
        this builder, to allow for chaining.

      • withSelection

        public PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder withSelection(String selection,
                                                   String[] selectionArgs)
        The selection and arguments to use. An occurrence of '?' in the selection will be replaced with the corresponding occurence of the selection argument. Any of the selection arguments may be overwritten by a selection argument back reference as specified by withSelectionBackReference(int, int). This can only be used with builders of type update, delete, or assert.
        返回:
        this builder, to allow for chaining.

      • withExpectedCount

        public PluginContentProviderOperation.Builder withExpectedCount(int count)
        If set then if the number of rows affected by this operation do not match this count OperationApplicationException will be throw. This can only be used with builders of type update, delete, or assert.
        返回:
        this builder, to allow for chaining.
